         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/7/92 ¶ Chevalier De Jardin ¶ Consul General for France ¶  ¶ Allow me, dear Consul, to send to you herewith fresh seeds of Atriplex vesicarium, in continuation of some former sendings of mine. As po...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.07.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Léon Dejardin</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Carton no. 12, Melbourne, consulat, Serie A, Centre des Archives Diplomatiques, Nantes.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by [Dejardin]: '28 juillet Rép. le même jour' [28 July, replied the same day]. Reply not found. For a printed version of this letter, see Home &amp; Maroske (1997), p. 33.</p>
               </note>28/7/92</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Chevalier De Jardin</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Consul General for France</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me, dear Consul, to send to you herewith fresh seeds of <name key="Atriplex%20vesicarium">Atriplex vesicarium</name>, in continuation of some former sendings of mine. As pointed out in my work on "Select plants for industrial culture and naturalisation" it is <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">this</hi>
               </seg> particular <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Saltbush</hi>
               </seg>, which is among the very best in the far interior for sheep-pasturage.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B91.09.01, pp. 59-60.</p>
               </note> As the French Government is desirous to test such kinds of plants on the stations, established in the Sahara and in other far inland-localities of North-Africa, I beg to offer this particular kind now. This Atriplex will bear slight frost, so that it might be naturalized even in South-France; but it will thrive best on ground somewhat saline.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Atriplex%20vesicarium">Atriplex vesicarium</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
